definitions.definition: A sending or mission (to do or accomplish something).
An official charge or authority to do something, often used of military officers.
examples: David received his commission after graduating from West Point.

definitions.definition: The thing to be done as agent for another.
examples: I have three commissions for the city.

definitions.definition: A body or group of people, officially tasked with carrying out a particular function .
examples: The company's sexual harassment commission made sure that every employee completed the on-line course.

definitions.definition: A fee charged by an agent or broker for carrying out a transaction.
examples: The real-estate broker charged a four percent commission for their knowledge on bidding for commercial properties; for their intellectual perspective on making a formal offer and the strategy to obtain a mutually satisfying deal with the seller in favour of the buyer.

definitions.definition: The act of committing (e.g. a crime or error).
examples: the commission , preparation or instigation of an act of terrorism
